<subSubSection id="C36696BB8E58FFB5FF1AFC09DBA3FBBA" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC3C5308E58FFB5FF1AFC09DBA3FBBA" blockId="3.[163,1070,1010,1116]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
Comment 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E58FFB5FEF4FC09DBC3FBE1" authority="oxyclypea" authorityName="oxyclypea KOCH" authorityYear="1934" box="[333,702,1010,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Schatzmayrina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oxyclypea" subSpecies="oxyclypea">
<emphasis id="B90819228E58FFB5FEF4FC09DBC3FBE1" box="[333,702,1010,1031]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Schatzmayrina oxyclypea oxyclypea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had previously been reported from the Afrotropical region, North Africa, and 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E58FFB5FDDDFBF4DBCDFBC2" box="[612,688,1039,1060]" name="Yemen" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Yemen</collectingCountry>
; for data and a distribution map see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E58FFB5FF1AFBD0D84BFBA6" author="PUTHZ V" box="[163,310,1066,1088]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" pagination="83 - 88" refId="ref7823" refString="PUTHZ V. (2007): First record of the euaesthetine genus Schatzmayrina KOCH in the Neotropics (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). - Mitteilungen des Internationalen Entomologischen Vereins Frankfurt a. M. 32 (3 / 4): 83 - 88." type="journal article" year="2007">PUTHZ (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. Two other subspecies are distributed in the 
<collectingRegion id="49B80BD28E58FFB5FCAAFBD1DAC9FBA6" box="[787,948,1066,1088]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
. The above specimens represent the first records from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E58FFB5FDEBFBBDDBA7FBBA" box="[594,730,1094,1116]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
